The paper focuses on the application of NeuroEvolution, a subfield of machine learning that combines neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for specific tasks, such as logic circuit design and digital gaming, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper proposes a new method for evolving neural networks, which involves encoding the network topology in a specific way, which could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also tests the proposed method on benchmark continuous learning environments, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
